HEADWORD: Heliometer
<hw>He`li*om"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Helio-</ets> + <ets>-meter</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>h⟦eacute⟧liom⟦egrave⟧tre</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>An
instrument devised originally for measuring the diameter of the sun; now
employed for delicate measurements of the distance and relative
direction of two stars too far apart to be easily measured in the field
of view of an ordinary telescope.</def></p>

<p><ent>Heliometrical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Heliometric</ent>⟦br⟧
